{"key":"processedPost-9927868","value":{"id":9927868,"first":9921161,"last":9927868,"when":1236451417,"utime":"03/07/09 08:43 PM","content":"NEVER use a 'frosting' layer.&nbsp; Agar tried it and failed.&nbsp; He made a post the first time it worked, but later realized like all of us do that it was a bad idea.&nbsp; Never leave grains exposed on the surface.&nbsp; They dry out and the mycelium stops growing, leaving the grain available to germinate trichoderma spores as soon as you mist the top, thus hydrating the grains/contaminants.<br />RR","title":"Re: Damn Contams","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}